uld assert that there's only one occurrence of the message. I’m also thinking about what happens if closure31 doesn’t execute or the detection fails—would that add another filter to the responseSpecification?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering code modifications**\\n\\nAs a coding assistant, I’m thinking about whether I should make an edit. I could add a test comment, but it seems unnecessary since we’ve already updated the test. For the third prompt, updating to invoke the generated class lookup like in existing tests crosses my mind, but it might risk a developer violation, and I definitely need to obey the guidelines. Also, using `ClassLoader.loadClass` isn't considered reflection itself; it’s dynamic class loading, which might also be prohibited.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "No further supported test refinement is available for this call site.\n\nI inspected the compiled active class and confirmed:\n\n- `RequestSpecificationImpl$_applyPathParamsAndSendRequest_closure31.doCall(...)` uses a direct class literal:\n  - `ldc class io/restassured/filter/log/ResponseLoggingFilter`\n- The reported dynamic-access call is inside the synthetic Groovy helper:\n  - `static Class class$(String)`\n  - which calls `Class.forName(String)`\n- That synthetic `class$` helper is not referenced by `doCall(...)` or by the enclosing request path in this artifact’s bytecode.\n\nThe existing test I added already exercises the supported public API path that creates and executes closure31:\n\n- validation-failure logging enabled\n- existing `ResponseLoggingFilter`\n- real Rest Assured request through `given().when().get(...).then()`\n\nHowever, the remaining uncovered call site is the unused synthetic helper itself, not the closure behavior. Reaching it would require directly invoking the generated internal `class$` method through reflection/`MethodHandles` or dynamic class-loading machinery, which would violate the test rules requiring normal public API coverage and no direct reflection.\n\nSo I left the public-API coverage test in place, but I did not add an artificial internal invocation for the unreachable synthetic `class$` call site.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01bc23ed220918b4016a27356ca99881968276fb926753de90\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 743, "output": 1830, "cacheRead": 36352, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38925, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780954410879, "responseId": "resp_01bc23ed220918b4016a27352b75d08196a613a7ea39a10504"}, "toolResults": []}
